  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Heavy (βεβαρημένοι)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The perfect participle. Lit., burdened or oppressed. \"It was but natural for these men of simple habits, at night, and after the long ascent, and in the strong mountain air, to be heavy with sleep; and we also know it as a psychological fact, that, in quick reaction, after the overpowering influence of the strongest emotions, drowsiness would creep over their limbs and senses\" (Edersheim). ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]